  "prompt": "What is the weather in Orlando like on June, and how does it differ from the weather in August?",
  "response": "The weather in Orlando during June is typically hot and humid, with average high temperatures around 90\u00b0F (32\u00b0C) and average low temperatures around 72\u00b0F (22\u00b0C). June also marks the beginning of the rainy season, so you can expect frequent afternoon thunderstorms and a significant amount of rainfall.\n\nIn August, the weather remains hot and humid, with average high temperatures again around 92\u00b0F (33\u00b0C), and average lows around 74\u00b0F (23\u00b0C). Like June, August is part of the rainy season, so thunderstorms and heavy rainfall are common. The frequency and intensity of the rain can be even higher in August.\n\nOverall, both June and August in Orlando are characterized by very warm temperatures and high humidity, along with frequent rains due to the rainy season. The main differences are that temperatures in August can be slightly higher, and the intensity and frequency of rainfall might be greater in August compared to June.",
